g.text: KP – Key PartnersAvailable· National aviation university· National ecological centrePotential· Ukrainian and international partner networks· Kyiv city state administration· Ministry for Ecology· Investors· Donors

KA – Key Activities· Development and production of sensors· Software development and support: both server and client· Training / support / consultation of clients (participants)· Curriculum and courses for students of environmental and engineering specialties· Enlightenment activity· Information and analytical activity

KR – Key ResourcesFor each functional group it is assumed availability of premises, equipment, human resources. There are the following groups:· Development, manufacture, maintenance of sensors· Development and maintenance of software· Uninterruptible server functioning support· Customer Service (helpdesk)· Logistics (purchase, sale, delivery from suppliers and to customers)· Management (processes, procedures, structural, legal, financial issues)

CS – Cost StructureStarting costs· Development of sensors· Software development: both server-side and client-side· Licensing, certification, attestation, calibrationOperational costs· Manufacture of sensors· Software support: both server-side and client-side· Rental servers, disk space, communication capabilities (cloud or dedicated)· Customer / participants support service / consultancy

CS – Consumers’ Segments· Ecologically conscious, active, disturbed individuals· Corporate customers· Municipal, regional and state authorities (departments of ecology)· Universities (departments of ecology, IT, engineering)· Related local, regional, global public "citizen science" like networks

RC – Relations with Clients· Creating a community with shared values, interests, lifestyles, such as device consumer / owners, joint discussions in network of generalized results, etc.· Personalized online consultation· Blog / discussion and advice forum· Clients (participants) seek to improve sensors (development and introduction of new types) and elements of the system· Scale the project (system) to new objects, territories, etc.· Electronic stock exchange of goods and services for the use and development of monitoring networks

SC – Sales channels· Online trade by goods and services· Conclusion of contracts for supply of goods and services· After-sales service· Selling / renting sensors via Internet· Development of systems (solutions) and delivery of kits of equipment

IF – Income FlowsFinancing Sources· State, regional, municipal environmental programs· International grants and projects· Donation and sponsorship fees· Investment contests (possibly Crowdfunding) at the stage of development / expansion of the project or its componentsResults of activity· Sales and service of sensors· Sale of accessories, indicator (on-screen, light, audio, etc.) devices or software applications· Rent or leasing of sensors· In-depth analytical report· Additional extension of functionality of the software part of the application· Contracts from corporate customers for installation of monitoring system for objects, territories, etc.

VP – Valuable Proposals· Individual independent capability in direct assessment of health risks by determining the environmental status of the air· Ability to exchange data with other participants, participation in public programs, use of data collected by all members of the network· Timely notification of each participant about bursts (exceeding of norms) of pollutants and a zone of high concentration in the city
Business model of air quality monitoring system AIRQM
